{"serial": "16003", "department_serial": 16, "code": "AR0035", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Renaissance Art and Culture", "ch": "文藝復興藝術與文化"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Wang,Juei-Ting"], "ch": ["王瑞婷"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "C2", "room": "204"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "藝術學研究所碩士班", "en": "MA in Art Studies"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 2, "selected": 39, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程為藝研所「藝術與視覺文化」微學程核心課程，將以四個單元「人文主義藝術概論」、「文藝復興的藝術類型」、「南方文藝復興專題」及「北方文藝復興專題」組成，配合期中考、觀影及討論、專題講座與口頭報告，總課程週數為十八週（十六加二彈性授課）。\n\n    文藝復興藝術與文化對大多數接受過大學前基礎教育學生而言，屬耳熟能詳的高階藝術（High Art）範疇的藝術欣賞，但此課程實則具結合科技、數位修復、展示、展演工具的創新跨領域學習。\n\n    課程預計目標為以下四項：\n\n    1. 透過文本閱讀，理解文藝復興關鍵思想內涵。\n    2. 觀看文藝復興藝術作品、城市、建築、古蹟、博物館等視覺遺存，培養分析作品的能力與藝術史知識。\n    3. 由以上兩項，更進一步對藝術家及藝術作品所處的時代脈絡及文化全景，養成深刻認識。\n    4. 對於文藝復興最重要的人文主義思想，除透過藝術及文化結晶之作理解外，亦能思考它在當代歷史與社會中的未來前景，重新認識人文學與藝術所具有的底蘊及再生能量。", "en": "1. To understand origins and rise of Humanism\n2. To analyse artistic developments and the emergence of the city-states\n3. To distinguish the northern Renaissance art, the southern Renaissance art, and the high Renaissance art"}, "outline": {"ch": "單元一 人文主義藝術的誕生\n第一週 課程介紹及說明\n第二週 複數的文藝復興：關鍵字源探析及作品巡禮\n第三週 中世紀之秋到文藝復興之春\n第四週 《神曲》的天堂、煉獄與地獄\n單元二 文藝復興的藝術類型\n第五週 濕壁畫與祭壇畫：朝聖、崇拜及戰爭\n第六週 【觀影與討論】\n第七週 【兒童節；民俗掃墓節放假1日】\n第八週 【期中測驗】\n第九週 【微光古樂集示範講座】＊提前至13點開始\n單元三 南方文藝復興專題\n第十週 煉金、巫術及宗教審判\n第十一週 透視法與視覺科學\n第十二週 解剖劇場與解剖插圖\n單元四 北方文藝復興專題\n第十三週 愚者頌、烏托邦及狂歡節\n第十四週 幻想、地域文化及藝術天才：波希與布魯格爾\n第十五週 【專題演講及論壇】\n第十六週 期末口頭報告", "en": "Week 1. Introduction\nWeek 2. What is the Renaissance?\nWeek 3. The Autumn of the Middle Ages and the Spring of t-he Renaissance\nWeek 4. Heaven, Purgatory and Hell in “Divina Commedia“\nWeek 5. Frescos and Altarpieces\nWeek 6. Conference I\nWeek 7. Children‘s Day (No classes on 4/4)\nWeek 8. Midterm\nWeek 9. Lecture: The Glean Ensemble\nWeek 10. Alchemy, Witchcraft, and the Inquisition\nWeek 11. Perspective and the Visual Science\nWeek 12. Anatomical Theatre\nWeek 13. “In Praise of Folly“ and “Utopia“\nWeek 14. Bosch and Brueghel\nWeek 15. Conference II\nWeek 16. Oral presentation"}, "textbook": {"ch": "1. Alan Bullock著，董樂山譯，《西方人文主義傳統》Humanist Tradition in the West（臺北：究竟出版社，2000）。\n2. Paul Johnson著，譚鐘瑜譯，《文藝復興：從黑暗中誕生的黃金年代》The Renaissance: A Short History（臺北：左岸文化，2004）。\n3. Jacob Burckhardt著，花亦芬譯，《義大利文藝復興時期的文化》 The Civilization of the Renaissance in Italy（臺北：聯經出版社，2007）。 \n4. Peter Burke著，賈士蘅譯，《知識社會史(上卷)：從古登堡到狄德羅》What is the History of Knowledge ? From Gutenberg to Diderot（臺北：麥田出版社，2003）。\n5. Johan Huizinga著，何道寬譯，《中世紀的秋天：14世紀和15世紀法國與荷蘭的生活、思想與藝術》The Autumn of the Middle Ages（廣州：花城出版社，2017）。\n6. Roy Porter著，巫毓荃譯，《瘋狂簡史》Madness: a Brief History（新北市：左岸文化，2018）。\n7. Charles G. Nauert Jr., Humanism and the Culture of the Renaissance Europe (Cambridge/New York : Cambridge University Press, 2006). \n8. Anthony Grafton and Lisa Jardin, From Humanism to the Humanities: Education and the Liberal Arts in Fifteenth and Sixteenth-Century Europe (Cambridge: Harvard University Press, 1986).\n9. John R. Hale, The Civilization of Europe in the Renaissance (New York: Touchstone, 1993).\n\nGrove Art Online, Artcyclopaedia 等網路資源\n＊其他教師自編講義", "en": "1. Alan Bullock著，董樂山譯，《西方人文主義傳統》Humanist Tradition in the West（臺北：究竟出版社，2000）。\n2. Paul Johnson著，譚鐘瑜譯，《文藝復興：從黑暗中誕生的黃金年代》The Renaissance: A Short History（臺北：左岸文化，2004）。\n3. Jacob Burckhardt著，花亦芬譯，《義大利文藝復興時期的文化》 The Civilization of the Renaissance in Italy（臺北：聯經出版社，2007）。 \n4. Peter Burke著，賈士蘅譯，《知識社會史(上卷)：從古登堡到狄德羅》What is the History of Knowledge ? From Gutenberg to Diderot（臺北：麥田出版社，2003）。\n5. Johan Huizinga著，何道寬譯，《中世紀的秋天：14世紀和15世紀法國與荷蘭的生活、思想與藝術》The Autumn of the Middle Ages（廣州：花城出版社，2017）。\n6. Roy Porter著，巫毓荃譯，《瘋狂簡史》Madness: a Brief History（新北市：左岸文化，2018）。\n7. Charles G. Nauert Jr., Humanism and the Culture of the Renaissance Europe (Cambridge/New York : Cambridge University Press, 2006). \n8. Anthony Grafton and Lisa Jardin, From Humanism to the Humanities: Education and the Liberal Arts in Fifteenth and Sixteenth-Century Europe (Cambridge: Harvard University Press, 1986).\n9. John R. Hale, The Civilization of Europe in the Renaissance (New York: Touchstone, 1993)."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "50％", "en": "50％"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n\n\n其他", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "", "", "Others"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "出席及課堂討論 40％；期中評量 30％；期末報告 30％。", "en": "40％Attendance, assignments and peer reviews\n30％ Midterm exam\n30％Research paper and Oral Presentation"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "週二上午9-12時", "en": "Tuesday, 9:00-12:00"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "十六週正式課程講述結束，十七、十八週為彈性調配週（講座或發表）", "en": "16-week semester"}, "domain": {"ch": "美學與藝術理論\n\n\n、\n\n\n西洋藝術史", "en": "美學與藝術理論\n\n\n、\n\n\n西洋藝術史"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "專業知能", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "邏輯與批判能力", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "語文表達與溝通", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "多元與國際視野", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "自主學習", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["專題研究報告(書面)", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "統合與創新能力", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Professional knowledge", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Logical and critical ability", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Ability to communicate clearly", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "A diverse and international vision", "ratin